# .leak-denylist — LOCAL, GITIGNORED. Copy to `.leak-denylist` and fill in YOUR values.
#
# `make leak-check` greps the whole tree for these strings (case-insensitive, fixed-string)
# and FAILS if any appears in a committed file. Put your installation-specific identifiers
# here so they can never leak into the public repo. This .example is committed; the real
# .leak-denylist is gitignored and never published — so the denylist never leaks the very
# strings it guards.
#
# One literal string (or IP prefix) per line. List YOUR real values in .leak-denylist, e.g.:
#   my-edge-hostname
#   my-laptop-hostname
#   me@example.com
#   203.0.113            # your VPS / relay public IP prefix
#   198.51.100           # your DNS upstream public IP prefix
#   <private ntfy topic or other capability tokens>
#   <hardware/disk UUIDs that identify your machine>
